# {{connectorName}}

Microsoft 365 Copilot Connector + Declarative Agent generated by **CopilotConnectorWorkflow**.

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| Connection ID | `{{connectorId}}` |
| ACL mode | `{{aclMode}}` |

## What's included

- **Copilot Connector** — ingests data into Microsoft 365 via the Microsoft Graph Connectors API
- **Declarative Agent** — `appPackage/declarativeAgent.json` uses this connector as a knowledge source
- **Fail-closed enhancer** — `src/custom/enhancer.ts` transforms raw items; enhancement errors never produce raw ingestion

## Prerequisites

| Requirement | Details |
|-------------|---------|
| VS Code + M365 Agents Toolkit | For F5 development; search "Microsoft 365 Agents Toolkit" in extensions |
| Node.js 18, 20, or 22 | Runtime |
| M365 Copilot license | Or [M365 Developer Program](https://developer.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/dev-program) tenant |
| Global Administrator | Required to grant admin consent |

## Quick start (F5 / Agents Toolkit)

1. Open this folder in VS Code
2. Install the **Microsoft 365 Agents Toolkit** extension
3. Press **F5** — the toolkit will:
   - Register the Entra ID app
   - Provision the connection + schema in Microsoft Graph
   - Start the Azure Functions host locally
4. Click the admin consent link shown in the terminal
5. Wait for schema registration (up to 10 minutes)
6. Enable inline results in M365 Admin Center → Search & intelligence → Data sources
7. Ask Copilot about your data

## Manual lifecycle (without Agents Toolkit)

```bash
npm install
npm run build

# Provision connection + register schema
npm run provision

# Ingest seed data (data/enhanced-items.jsonl)
npm run ingest

# Start functions locally
npm start
```

Set credentials in `local.settings.json`:

| Key | Value |
|-----|-------|
| `TENANT_ID` | Entra tenant ID |
| `CLIENT_ID` | App registration client ID |
| `CLIENT_SECRET` | Client secret (blank for managed identity) |
| `USE_MANAGED_IDENTITY` | `true` to use managed identity |
| `DATA_SOURCE_PATH` | JSONL file path (default `./data/enhanced-items.jsonl`) |
| `ACL_MODE` | `everyone`, `everyoneExceptGuests`, or `none` |

## Connecting a live data source

Replace `src/custom/dataSource.ts`'s `fetchRawItems()` with calls to your live API or database.
The crawl function in `src/functions/crawl.ts` calls `enhance()` on each raw item before ingesting.

**FAIL CLOSED**: if `enhance()` throws `EnhancementError`, the item is skipped and never ingested raw.

## Security

Use managed identity in production (`USE_MANAGED_IDENTITY=true`). Store secrets in Key Vault.
The default ACL mode is `{{aclMode}}` — review before deploying with non-public data.

